00897 # ifndef yytnamerr
00898 /* Copy to YYRES the contents of YYSTR after stripping away unnecessary
00899    quotes and backslashes, so that it's suitable for yyerror.  The
00900    heuristic is that double-quoting is unnecessary unless the string
00901    contains an apostrophe, a comma, or backslash (other than
00902    backslash-backslash).  YYSTR is taken from yytname.  If YYRES is
00903    null, do not copy; instead, return the length of what the result
00904    would have been.  */
00905 static YYSIZE_T
00906 yytnamerr (char *yyres, const char *yystr)
00907 {
00908   if (*yystr == '"')
00909     {
00910       YYSIZE_T yyn = 0;
00911       char const *yyp = yystr;
00912 
00913       for (;;)
00914         switch (*++yyp)
00915           {
00916           case '\'':
00917           case ',':
00918             goto do_not_strip_quotes;
00919 
00920           case '\\':
00921             if (*++yyp != '\\')
00922               goto do_not_strip_quotes;
00923             /* Fall through.  */
00924           default:
00925             if (yyres)
00926               yyres[yyn] = *yyp;
00927             yyn++;
00928             break;
00929 
00930           case '"':
00931             if (yyres)
00932               yyres[yyn] = '\0';
00933             return yyn;
00934           }
00935     do_not_strip_quotes: ;
00936     }
00937 
00938   if (! yyres)
00939     return yystrlen (yystr);
00940 
00941   return yystpcpy (yyres, yystr) - yyres;
